        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "Activation of the STAT3 pathway downstream of ALK signaling contributes to cellular survival by modulating expression of a number of genes involved in apoptosis, immune response and angiogenesis (reviewed in Werner et al, 2009). The STAT3 pathway is particularly important in ALK+ cancers that express ALK fusion proteins, where STAT3 contributes to the repression of a number of tumor suppressor genes, highlighting its role as a critical oncogene (reviewed in Yu et al, 2014; Guanizo et al, 2018)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "STAT3 nuclear events downstream of ALK signaling" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Reviewed: Turner, Suzanne, 2023-11-08" , "Authored: Rothfels, Karen, 2021-03-30" , "Reviewed: Inghirami, Giorgio, 2021-05-04" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Rothfels, Karen, 2021-03-30" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
